p.m:
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    -\frac{14}{15} \cdot \left(-\frac{19}{28}\right)
    \amp = \frac{14}{15} \cdot \frac{19}{28}\amp \hbox{We can divide both the first numerator and second denominator by 14.}\\
    \amp = \frac{1}{15} \cdot \frac{19}{2}\\
    \amp = \frac{19}{30}
    \end{aligned} }
